{"info": {"author": "Diarmuid Collins", "author_email": "diarmuid.m.collins+github@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# Newkiton \n\nI bought a temperature senson on Amazon (https://www.amazon.com/Newkiton-NK-01B-Thermometer-Temperature-Compatible/dp/B07W53L4RD) \nI wanted to integrate it into a Graphana dashboard and to do so I needed to figure out how to pull the data from it\n\nWith that in mind, I reverse engineered the protocol. At the moment I know the basic on how to get the temperatire readings \nfrom the device and not much more.\n\nI am not that familar with BLE but I know wireshark so I used that to reverse engineer it. The  I just copied the \nprotocol and came up with this\n\nThe device seems to store the data on a NVM with a simple address scheme. I presume it wraps around but I haven't \nrun it for long enough just yet.\n\nTo use this, just instanciate a device and call the temperature method. The temperature is only updated every 10 minutes \nso call it more frequently will only return a cached version\n\n`````python\nfrom Newkiton import Newkiton\nimport time\n\nsensor = Newkiton.Newkiton(deviceAddr=\"8e:f9:00:00:00:ed\")\nwhile True:\n    print(\"Temp={}\".format(sensor.temperature()))\n    time.sleep(60*10)\n\n\n`````\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/diarmuid/Newkiton", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "Newkiton", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Newkiton/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Newkiton/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/diarmuid/Newkiton"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Newkiton/0.0.6/", "requires_dist": ["bluepy"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Newkiton temperature sensor", "version": "0.0.6", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Newkiton</h1>\n<p>I bought a temperature senson on Amazon (<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Newkiton-NK-01B-Thermometer-Temperature-Compatible/dp/B07W53L4RD\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.amazon.com/Newkiton-NK-01B-Thermometer-Temperature-Compatible/dp/B07W53L4RD</a>)\nI wanted to integrate it into a Graphana dashboard and to do so I needed to figure out how to pull the data from it</p>\n<p>With that in mind, I reverse engineered the protocol. At the moment I know the basic on how to get the temperatire readings\nfrom the device and not much more.</p>\n<p>I am not that familar with BLE but I know wireshark so I used that to reverse engineer it. The  I just copied the\nprotocol and came up with this</p>\n<p>The device seems to store the data on a NVM with a simple address scheme. I presume it wraps around but I haven't\nrun it for long enough just yet.</p>\n<p>To use this, just instanciate a device and call the temperature method. The temperature is only updated every 10 minutes\nso call it more frequently will only return a cached version</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">Newkiton</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Newkiton</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">time</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">sensor</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Newkiton</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Newkiton</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">deviceAddr</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"8e:f9:00:00:00:ed\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"k\">while</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"Temp=</span><span class=\"si\">{}</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">format</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">sensor</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">temperature</span><span class=\"p\">()))</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sleep</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">60</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6741991, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "4c89ddec36954b22a9871deb588d1155", "sha256": "ec03b1a72d581bd032375effa7898466a31bc2c16ec8538dc2abb557bee1eb3d"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Newkiton-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "4c89ddec36954b22a9871deb588d1155", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 16519, "upload_time": "2020-02-24T21:24:54", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-24T21:24:54.984251Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/89/a9/579309e2da8f330d061a12dc71f1c53cb6e4874f80cf0beef78ea649ecc8/Newkiton-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c4076b0974d7e00d7a3baff72848a7dd", "sha256": "984d784281eaecb3b95703ff0ae91253bbfe6b1435e8a620ad7f76a78cc5d076"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Newkiton-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c4076b0974d7e00d7a3baff72848a7dd", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3318, "upload_time": "2020-02-24T21:24:57", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-24T21:24:57.207942Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/a4/23/d7cc5212d2c13b7d93a92ca20182605d4c5e91093636ef8a32978a808af3/Newkiton-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "770de5c0a094c7cd73986eb796528fb0", "sha256": "c1e1e3bec3f21787a4c8530f4fd56d6adde59105a7067ca7c14e1fc3a3193f2c"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Newkiton-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, 